<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1898-04-20T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1898-04-20T00:00:00-05:00" n="628" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d628">
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">Señor <persName type="from">Polo de Bernabé</persName>
                                to Mr. <persName type="to">Sherman</persName>.</hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Translation.]</seg></opener>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Legation of Spain at Washington</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1898-04-20"><hi rend="italic">April 20, 1898</hi></date>.
                                (Received 11.35 a.m.)</dateline></opener>
                        <p><hi rend="smallcaps">Mr. Secretary</hi>: The resolution adopted by the
                            Congress of the United States of America, and approved to-day by the
                            President, is of such a nature that my continuance in Washington becomes
                            impossible and obliges me to request you the delivery of my
                            passports.</p>
                        <p>The protection of Spanish interests will be intrusted to the French
                            ambassador and to the Austro-Hungarian minister.<note n="1" xml:id="d628fn1">See <ref target="#pg_785">page
                            785</ref>.</note></p>
                        <p>On this occasion, very painful to me, I have, etc.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Luis Polo de Bernabé.</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>